On 22 March, after a telephone conversation with Prime Minister Giuseppe Conté of Italy, Russian President Vladimir Putin organized the dispatch to Italy of Russian military paramedics, specialized disinfectant transport and other medical equipment.
The Italian newspaper La Stampa quotes an anonymous "high-level political source," claiming that 80 per cent of Russian aid was "unhelpful or of little use to Italy."
